class Client {
}

class Target {
  + targetMethod1 : ??
  + targetMethod2 : ??
}

class Adaptor {
  + adaptee: Adaptee
  + targetMethod1() : ??
  + targetMethod2() : ??
}

class Adaptee {
  + methodA() : ??
  + methodB() : ??
  + methodC() : ??
}

Client --> Target : uses
Adaptor --|> Target : extends
Adaptor o--> Adaptee : has

note right of Client
  <b>Client</b>
  Uses the Target interface
end note

note right of Target
  <b>Target</b>
  Defines the interface that Client uses
end note

note right of Adaptor
  <b>Adaptor</b>
  Implements Target interface
  and wraps Adaptee
end note

note right of Adaptee
  <b>Adaptee</b>
  Existing class with incompatible interface
end note

@enduml